TITLE: Defiant Taiwanese ready if China invades, say there's only one possible response
SUMMARY: Fox News Digital spoke to ordinary Taiwanese citizens in the capital city of Taipei about the threat of a Chinese invasion against the island nation.

TITLE: Putin expands fast-track Russian citizenship process for all Ukrainians
SUMMARY: A process for speedily obtaining Russian citizenship is now available to all Ukrainians following a decree signed by Russian President Vladimir Putin on Monday.

TITLE: Chinese cops 'beat' protesters outraged at having bank accounts frozen
SUMMARY: Police in China beat protesters who rallied against having millions of dollars in their bank accounts wrongly frozen over COVID-19 policies, protesters stated Monday.

TITLE: Boris Johnson resignation will not impact UK support for Ukraine: experts
SUMMARY: British and Ukrainian officials believe that cooperation between their nations will remain strong regardless of which leader takes over from Boris Johnson as prime minister.

TITLE: Chinese bank depositors face police in angry protest
SUMMARY: Chinese bank depositors faced off against security and plain clothed police as they protested for access to accounts that had been frozen and locked away.

TITLE: Ukraine war: Russian rocket attack kills 15, dozens more trapped under rubble
SUMMARY: The Russian missile strike killed 15 people so far, with rescue services in communication with at least 3 survivors among the dozens trapped under the rubble.

TITLE: Dutch farmers form 'freedom convoys' to protest government's strict environmental rules
SUMMARY: Thousands of Dutch farmers have formed their version of "Freedom Convoys" to protest the government's new goals aimed to cut nitrogen and ammonia emissions by 50% by 2030.

TITLE: South Korea detects shots apparently launched by North Korea
SUMMARY: South Korea said it detected trajectories of what appeared to be shots fired by North Korea on Sunday, with the military strengthening surveillance and alert levels.

TITLE: At least 19 dead in pair of mass shootings in South Africa, police confirm
SUMMARY: Two mass shootings in South Africa left at least 19 people killed and an unknown number of people injured late Saturday. Police say the shooters were "firing randomly."

TITLE: South Africa police say 14 dead in bar shooting in Soweto
SUMMARY: Authorities in Johannesburg's Soweto township say 14 people were killed and three others were wounded during a mass shooting at a bar Saturday night.

TITLE: Sri Lankan president, prime minister to resign after protesters storm residences, set fire
SUMMARY: Sri Lanka's Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe will resign after thousands of protesters stormed the president's house amid the country's economic struggles.

TITLE: Taiwan loses major advocate, defensive ally with assassination of Shinzo Abe
SUMMARY: With the death of former Prime Minister of Japan Shinzo Abe, Taiwan has lost a key supporter in its political and defensive standoff against the Chinese Communist Party.

TITLE: Russia moves reservist forces near Ukraine for offensive operations: UK defense ministry
SUMMARY: Russia is moving its reserve forces to Ukraine's border in what UK intelligence warns is in preparation for future offensive operations.

TITLE: Chinese foreign ministry says Abe assassination 'should not be associated with Sino-Japanese relations'
SUMMARY: A spokesperson for the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs released a statement denying “association” with former Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe's assassination.

TITLE: Israeli NGO says journalist killed by Palestinians, not by Israeli soldier
SUMMARY: An Israeli legal civil rights group has placed new question marks over the U.S. State Department and Palestinian accounts of who killed an Al Jazeera reporter.

TITLE: Ukrainian 'volunteer recruits' arrive in UK for military training in move to bolster resistance against Russia
SUMMARY: Ukrainian soldiers have arrived in the UK to begin basic soldier training in a new military program that will train up green recruits.

TITLE: Shinzo Abe assassination: Pope Francis sends telegram of 'heartfelt condolences' to Japan
SUMMARY: Pope Francis offered his 'heartfelt condolences" to the people of Japan after former Prime Minister Shinzo Abe was assassinated Thursday in Nara prefecture.

TITLE: Ukraine military sees spike in female volunteers amid war with Russia
SUMMARY: Ukraine's military has seen a spike in the number of female volunteers looking to join its ranks amid its deadly war with Russia.

TITLE: China: Knife attack at Shanghai hospital leaves four injured
SUMMARY: Four people were injured in a knife attack at a hospital in Shanghai, China, police said. Videos taken at the scene show hospital staff fleeing a bloddied crime scene.

TITLE: Boris Johnson resigns: What's next for UK
SUMMARY: U.K. Prime Minister Boris Johnson is stepping down from his position. As a leader favored by former President Donald Trump, Johnson was dubbed "Britain's Trump."
